Package: easyML
Type: Package
Title: Easy Machine Learning in R
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-01-22
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jose", "Ventura-Leon",
           email = "jventuraleon@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2996-4244"))
    )
Description: Estimates the minimum sample size needed to achieve a target
    performance in Machine Learning models using Monte Carlo simulation and
    learning curves. Implements power-law curve fitting for extrapolation,
    supports multiple test partitions for robustness assessment, bootstrap
    confidence intervals for uncertainty quantification, and comprehensive
    fit diagnostics. The methodology follows Ventura-Leon (2026) and provides
    tools similar to G*Power but designed specifically for machine learning
    applications in the social, health, and behavioral sciences.
